article.headline: Arizona St. 88, Stanford 70
article.story: TEMPE, Ariz. -- Ty Abbott scored 29 points and had a career-high 12 rebounds as Arizona State defeated Stanford 88-70 on Saturday to keep the Cardinal winless on the road. Derek Glasser had 12 points and 10 assists for the Sun Devils (15-7, 5-4 Pac-10), who had dropped the first two games of a three-game homestand. Landry Fields, tied for the Pac-10 scoring lead, had 22 points for the Cardinal, (10-11, 4-5), who fell to 0-8 on the road. Abbott hit six 3-pointers in the first 10 minutes as Arizona State raced to a 41-11 lead, and the Sun Devils coasted from there, leading by as many as 37 points. He finished 11 of 14 from the floor and 7 of 9 from beyond the arc.
